title: SFH to attend World Health Assembly
content_text:
p>
	The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, will depart for London, 
	the United Kingdom (UK), early tomorrow (May 16) for a duty visit regarding 
	the regulation of doctors' professional practice and medical devices, as 
	well as to learn more about the UK's development of authentication and 
	certification services for Chinese medicine. After visiting London, Dr Ko 
	will attend the 67th World Health Assembly (WHA) of the World Health

will attend the 67th World Health Assembly (WHA) of the World Health 
	Organization in Geneva, Switzerland. While in London, Dr Ko will pay a visit to the General Medical Council, 
	which serves as an independent regulator of UK doctors and follows up on 
	serious cases of professional misconduct that may affect doctors' 
	registration. He will also call on the Chairman of the Medicines and 
	Healthcare Products Regulatory Agency (MHRA), Sir Gordon Duff. The MHRA is a 
	UK government agency responsible for the regulation of medicines and medical

UK government agency responsible for the regulation of medicines and medical 
	devices and equipment used in healthcare procedures. Dr Ko will also visit the Royal Botanical Gardens (Kew Gardens) in London. 
	He will tour the laboratories and medicinal plants in the garden to learn 
	more about the Chinese medicine authentication and certification services 
	there. He will leave London for Geneva on May 18 (London time) to attend the 67th 
	WHA on May 19 (Geneva time) as a member of the China delegation. Dr Ko will
arrive back in Hong Kong on the afternoon of May 20.
